{"cursor":"3095","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Jack Gaughan' (September 24, 1930 - July 21, 1985) was an American science\nfiction artist and illustrator who won the Hugo Award several times. Working\nprimarily with Donald A. Wollheim at Ace Books and later DAW Books, and also\n[[Galaxy Magazine]] during the late 1960s, his simple linear style brought to\nlife unforgettable images of such classics as Andre Norton's [[Witch World]]\nNovels and Edward Elmer Smith's [[Lensmen]] and Skylark novels (for which he did\ntwo related sets of Pyramid Books covers). His broad visual vocabulary enabled\nhim to render the objects, spaceships and scenes in whatever was presented to\nhim as they were described in the books and stories he illustrated. That was\nespecially an accomplishment as many of these authors drew on their knowledge of\nvery esoteric subjects for their imagery. This ability made him very popular\namong people with an engineering background.\n\nDuring most of Ejler Jakobsson's tenure at [[Galaxy Magazine]] from 1969 to 1974\nhe did all the illustration and much of the design that went on in the magazine.\nIn addition, many of the books he did for Ace featured frontispieces, hand-\nlettered titled pages or maps at the front with Gaughan's distinctive\ncalligraphy. An example would be Alan Garner's [[The Weirdstone of\nBrisingamen]]. L. Sprague de Camp's 1967 anthology, [[The Fantastic Swordsmen]]\nincluded a Gaughan map before each of the stories in it. Notably, he illustrated\nthe covers and hand-lettered title pages for the Ace Books' edition of J. R. R.\nTolkien's [[The Lord of the Rings]].\n\nAs well as his professional work, he was a frequent contributor to SF fan\nmagazines. [[Locus (magazine)|Locus]] ran a column by him for a while, and in\nhis heyday he was often nominated for Hugo Awards for both professional artist\nand best fan artist simultaneously.\n\nIn his memory, the New England Science Fiction Association presents the '[[Jack\nGaughan Award]]' for best emerging sf illustrator.\n","linknr":128,"url":"Jack_Gaughan","recorded":1375088768,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Jack_Gaughan&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Jack_Gaughan&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Hugo_Award","/wiki/Donald_A._Wollheim","/wiki/Ace_Books","/wiki/DAW_Books","/wiki/Galaxy_Magazine","/wiki/Andre_Norton","/wiki/Witch_World","/wiki/Edward_Elmer_Smith","/wiki/Lensmen","/wiki/Pyramid_Books","/wiki/Ejler_Jakobsson","/wiki/Galaxy_Magazine","/wiki/Book_frontispiece","/wiki/Alan_Garner","/wiki/The_Weirdstone_of_Brisingamen","/wiki/L._Sprague_de_Camp","/wiki/The_Fantastic_Swordsmen","/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien","/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings","/wiki/Locus_(magazine)","/wiki/Hugo_Award","/wiki/New_England_Science_Fiction_Association","/wiki/Jack_Gaughan_Award","/w/index.php?title=Jack_Gaughan&action=edit&section=1","http://alphecca.com/archives/gaughan.html","http://www.unknowntrails.com/coversSF/Koontz-Darkness.html","http://users.telerama.com/~taliesen/tolkien/oop-lotr.html","http://www.berserkerfan.org/gaughanart.htm","http://www.isfdb.org/cgi-bin/ea.cgi?Jack_Gaughan","/wiki/Internet_Speculative_Fiction_Database","/wiki/Authority_control","/wiki/Virtual